channel.title: Voidz Client
channel.description:
Base :- MITB non packaged client Type :- 317 loading 377 Refactored or Not :- Refactored
Information :- Well i got the blank client a while ago and it was basically just in my Documents doing nothing. So i cleared a lot of my computer got to it and just thought oh what the hell I'll mess around with it see what happens lol. I started editing the Cache uploading the newer icons and made it look like one of the old RuneScape gameframes it sounds easy and quite frankly it was the only hard part was aligning the sideicons properly onto the backbase but that's as far as i went i might make something of this client at some point but I'm releasing so you guys can do what you want with it.. Yes this is refactored.
Screenshot:
[img]http://img13.imageshack.us/img13/2317/voidz1.png[/img]
Download Link :- [url=http://"http://www.mediafire.com/download.php?jtzyzmmdmvj"]Here[/url]
~Voidz

item.dc:creator: @LolPigeon LolPigeon
item.description:
@LolPigeon wrote:

[quote=“primadude, post:7, topic:287325”][quote author=I Voidz I link=topic=379931.msg2860650#msg2860650 date=1247143186]
Renamed = WIN!
[/quote]

How Refactored better than non-refactored? Refactoring a client just dumbs it down for people, and makes it more understandable. It takes a better memory and probably more skill to edit a non-refactored client.[/quote]

It doesn’t ‘dumb it down’ at all. In fact it helps you learn more.
Quite frankly the people that use non-refactored clients are retarded. Using something that is harder to edit doesn’t make you smarter, and doesn’t mean you have more skill.
It’s like saying notepad is better than an IDE because it’s harder to program with…
